(63, 1, '2018-09-18 01:39:39', '2018-09-18 01:39:39', 'To be able to access the Patient Portal you need to have our front office staff send you an email with an invitation to do so. By clicking on the link in the email you will be taken to our web site and be able to set up your password to access your medical information. To create a password you will need to have your chart account number from the office.\r\n\r\nOnce you have logged in you will be able to access considerable amounts of information.\r\n\r\nOn the left sided column you will have the categories of;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"auto-style3\">Inbox and chart documents;</span>The chart documents hold documents that have medical information, such as labs, x-rays or pathology. If there is information that you know is in the chart and is not listed, it is because it has not been enabled for access. Some of the documents cannot be enabled.</li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"auto-style3\">The inbox:</span>allows you to send a message to any member of the office staff with your question.</li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"auto-style3\">My Demographics</span>; which you can access and change. There are other options as well.</li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"auto-style3\">My Medical information;</span>When you click on this button a drop down menu presents itself on top of the main page. This allows you to view data that is contained in tabular format including vital signs and recomendations from your last visit. You can also access your appointment history. Some of the fields are not user friendly and being worked upon...</li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"auto-style3\">Clinical summaries;</span>These are generated after your visit and has some of the information pertaining to your health and visit. We would like you to view this clinical summary. It is work in progress,... and is being refined over time.</li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"auto-style3\">Change your password;</span>self explanatory.</li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"auto-style3\">Statement:</span>We are not using this feature yet.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe want you to experiment with the site and tell us what works for you and what doesn\'t. With feedback to our electronic health care provider we can hopefully become more relevant and user friendly.\r\n\r\nPlease recognize that this is work in progress and we appreciatte your patience with the issues we are sure you will encounter.', 'Portal Instructions', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'portal-instructions', '', '', '2018-09-18 01:39:39', '2018-09-18 01:39:39', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/?page_id=63', 0, 'page', '', 0),
