(66, 1, '2018-09-18 01:40:48', '2018-09-18 01:40:48', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-168 alignleft\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/20180928_Environmental_Portraits-2-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" />The field of pulmonary medicine deals with respiration and all the steps that are involved with it.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Symptoms for which people come in for evaluation include coughing, chest pain, shortness of breath, decreased ability to exercise, dizziness and other complaints. At times, an exam of the abdomen or chest for some unrelated reason can find something that requires the attention of our services. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cellular respiration takes place in the cells of our body where oxygen and nutrients become energy and is converted into carbon dioxide. Our bodies have developed systems to deal with bringing the oxygen from the air and eliminate carbon dioxide from our tissues through the lungs. The oxygen is delivered through the blood to tissues by the pumping action of the heart. At the same time the carbon dioxide is brought back to the lungs to be eliminated. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Respiratory medicine studies and manages diseases and disorders affecting respiration and the organs involved in this vital function.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Disorders that involve the airways that allow the air to come in and out of the lung tissue include asthma, COPD, bronchiectasis, upper airway obstruction and others. Diseases of the lung tissue where oxygen exchange takes place include emphysema and interstitial lung disease.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pulmonary medicine also frequently involves diagnosing and treating the part of the heart that pumps blood through the lungs and then to the tissues where the cellular respiration takes place. Disorders such as pulmonary embolism and pulmonary hypertension fall into this category. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In addition, masses or abnormal shadows in the lung are sometimes found that need to be evaluated. Those can be valley fever, lung cancer, pneumonia or a variety of other conditions. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Pulmonary', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'pulmonary', '', '', '2018-10-06 22:02:37', '2018-10-06 22:02:37', '', 72, 'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/?page_id=66', 0, 'page', '', 0),
