(68, 1, '2018-09-18 01:40:48', '2018-09-18 01:40:48', '<p class=\"auto-style3\">The field of pulmonary medicine cover diseases that affect the respiratory system. This includes a broad spectrum of conditions and diagnosis.</p>\r\n<p class=\"auto-style3\">As there is considerable overall with the other other aspects of the person\'s physiology this is a specialty that requires expertise in the functioning of various other physiological processes. In particular cardiovascular, hematological, endocrine and neurological function.</p>\r\n<p class=\"auto-style3\">From a physiological point of view the main function of the respiratory system is to participate in the delivery of oxygen from the atmosphere to the tissues and the removal of carbon dioxide from the body (the end result of cellular respiration).</p>\r\n<p class=\"auto-style3\">The respiratory system encompasses from the nasal passages and airways to deliver air intho the alveoli to the pulmonary circulation.</p>\r\n<p class=\"auto-style3\">The right side of the heart pumps blood through the pulmonary circulation thereby delivering carbon dioxide into the alveoli and allowing the blood to carry the oxygen to rest of the body.</p>\r\n<p class=\"auto-style3\">The air moves in and out of the chest through the pumping action of the respiratory muscles acting on the skeleton, the amount of ventilation finely tuned to the needs of the body.</p>\r\n<p class=\"auto-style3\">The lungs can be roughly divided into 3 major components;</p>\r\n<p class=\"auto-style3\">1: A system of pipes to deliver the air in and out of the lungs.</p>\r\n<p class=\"auto-style3\">2: A pulmonary tissue to allow passage of oxygen from the air to the blood and carbon dioxide from the blood to the alveolar air.</p>\r\n<p class=\"auto-style3\">3: Pulmonary circulation to deliver the blood to the lungs and from there to the left heart and the general circulation.</p>\r\n<p class=\"auto-style3\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"auto-style3\">In the following page I have a picture roughly describing the anatomy..</p>', 'Pulmonary', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '66-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-18 01:40:48', '2018-09-18 01:40:48', '', 66, 'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/2018/09/18/66-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(69, 1, '2018-09-18 01:41:54', '2018-09-18 01:41:54', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sleep is a state of partial dissociation form our environment.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Some of the complaints that patients have when they see us are difficulty falling or staying asleep, snoring, un-refreshing sleep and daytime sleepiness. At times, a sleep study done for evaluation of atrial fibrillation detects sleep apnea that needs to be addressed.</span>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When we sleep, we go through different stages described as REM and non-REM sleep. Though the mechanisms are not understood, sleep isincreasingly becoming recognized as a major contributor to overall health. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Good sleep allows us to stay alert and focused when we need to, and plays a major role in memory and emotional well being. Lack of sleep or poor sleep is also believed to be associated with a variety of cardiovascular issues and immune system malfunction, among other health problems. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sleep Medicine diagnoses and treats disorders that interfere with the quality of sleep, as well as disorders of poor daytime alertness and excessive sleepiness. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Some of these conditions can be the results of disorders that do not allow us to sleep well, such as obstructive or central apnea. Poor sleep habits or work schedules may result in insufficient sleep. A variety of other disorders that interfere with sleep include restless leg syndrome, REM behavior disorder and insomnia. Narcolepsy is an example of a disorder that typically leads to attacks of severe sleepiness when the person should be awake.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Sleep', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'sleep', '', '', '2018-09-30 20:21:56', '2018-09-30 20:21:56', '', 72, 'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/?page_id=69', 0, 'page', '', 0),
