(97, 1, '2018-09-19 01:51:15', '2018-09-19 01:51:15', 'Dr Giron was born in Saint Louis Mo, while his father was completing his surgical residency. His parents had come from Argentina, but when the training was finished they wanted to move back to their home country. They moved to the small town of Bariloche in Southwest Patagonia. As a result Dr Giron grew up in a resort town known for its chocolate, mountains, lakes, fishing, skiing, and many outdoor activities.\r\n\r\nAt the urgings of his parents he went to study medicine in Buenos Aires far away from his home town paradise. Argentinas political climate was turbulent and uncertain during the 1970s. Despite the shock of living in a metropolis he stuck with his studies and eventually graduated with his MD degree.\r\n\r\nCurious and ambitious and not wanting to live in Buenos Aires he decided to see what he could find in his birth country. In the US he travelled from one end to the other of the country and was amazed by the size of the US and the number of huge cities that dotted the landscape.\r\n\r\nThrough various friendships and connections he ended up in an Internal Medicine Internship in Washington DC. He lived in the area for 4 years after completing 3 years of training and 1 year of chief resident.\r\n\r\nHe found Internal Medicine challenging and decided to pursue the specialty of Pulmonary Diseases. He also decided he wanted to get back to a more mountainous area and as result visited various training programs. Eventually got accepted at the Pulmonary Fellowship training program in the VAMC in Long Beach. His training in Pulmonary Medicine included Sleep medicine as well as Intensive care medicine.\r\n\r\nThe program included time in Long Beach Memorial Hospital, UCI, and City of Hope in addition to the VA. He gained alot of experience and was exposed to different patient populations. He decided to try an academic career for one year, but decided that he wanted to be more directly involved with patient care.\r\n\r\nIn 1989 he was hired by the Lombard Medical Group in Thousand Oaks and moved to the area. He had an excellent experience with the group, but in 1993 was ready to start his own medical practice.\r\n\r\nOver the many years working in the community he has been involved in the care of countless patients in the areas of his expertise. He greatly enjoys working and always learning. He considers many of his patients his friends and loves to be able to help them.\r\n\r\nFor years he has been working in close partnership with his wife on his medical practice as well as their family. He is blessed to have a great staff as well.\r\n\r\nHe likes to be active and busy. When not working he enjoys reading, working on the computer, running, biking, hiking, skiing, playing ping-pong, and hanging out with his family. He has found the area of Thousand Oaks and the state of California a perfect match for his lifestyle. He has an active social life and never has enough time to do all the things he would like to.\r\n\r\nAbove all things he is a very proud father. Both his daughter and son are doing very well and are his greatest life achievement', 'Dr. Andres Giron', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'dr-andres-giron', '', '', '2018-10-06 22:24:32', '2018-10-06 22:24:32', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/?post_type=profile&#038;p=97', 0, 'profile', '', 0),
