(148, 1, '2018-09-30 19:55:12', '2018-09-30 19:55:12', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The field of Pulmonary medicine deals with respiration and all the steps that are involved with it. Cellular respiration takes place in the cells of our body where oxygen and nutrients become energy and is converted into carbon dioxide. Our bodies have developed systems to deal with bringing the oxygen from the air and eliminate carbon dioxide from our tissues through the lungs. The oxygen is delivered through the blood to the tissues attached to the hemoglobin by the pumping action of the heart. At the same time the carbon dioxide is brought back to the lungs to be eliminated. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Respiratory medicine studies and manages the diseases involving diseases and disorders affecting respiration and the organs involved in this vital function. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Disorders that involve the airways that allow the air to come in and out of the lung tissue include asthma, COPD, bronchiectasis, upper airway obstruction and others. Examples of diseases of the lung tissue where oxygen exchange takes place are emphysema, interstitial lung disease and others are seen frequently. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pulmonary medicine also frequently has to diagnose and treat the part of the heart that has to pump the blood through the lungs and then to the systemic circulation so it can reach the tissues where the cellular respiration takes place. Disorders such as pulmonary embolism and pulmonary hypertension fall into this category. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At times masses or abnormal shadows in the lung are found that need to be evaluated. Sometimes they are found to be valley fever, lung cancer, pneumonia or a variety of other conditions. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Symptoms for which people come in for evaluation include; cough, chest pain, shortness of breath, decreased ability to exercise, dizziness and other complaints. At times the incidental finding on a CT of the abdomen or chest done for some other reason require the attention of our services. </span>', 'Pulmonary', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '66-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-30 19:55:12', '2018-09-30 19:55:12', '', 66, 'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/2018/09/30/66-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(150, 1, '2018-09-30 19:55:28', '2018-09-30 19:55:28', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sleep is a state of partial dissociation form our environment. While we sleep we go through different stages of sleep described as REM and non-REM sleep. Though the mechanisms are not understood, sleep is becoming increasingly recognized as a major contributor to overall health. Good sleep allows us to stay alert and focused when we need to, and plays a major role in memory and emotional well being. Lack of sleep or poor sleep is also believed to be associated with a variety of cardiovascular issues and immune system malfunction among other. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sleep Medicine addresses disorders that interfere with the quality of sleep as well as disorders of poor daytime alertness and excessive sleepiness. Some of these conditions can be the results of disorders that do not allow us to sleep well such as obstructive or central apnea. Poor sleep habits or work schedules may result in insufficient sleep. A variety of other disorders that interfere with sleep include restless leg syndrome, REM behavior disorder, insomnia and others. Narcolepsy is an example of a disorder that typically leads to attacks of severe sleepiness while the person should be awake.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sleep Medicine deals with trying to make a diagnosis and help treat these disorders. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Some of the complaints that patients come to see us are difficulty initiating, maintaining sleep, snoring, un-refreshing sleep and daytime sleepiness and others. At times a sleep study done for evaluation of atrial fibrillation detects significant obstructive sleep apnea that needs to be addressed. </span>', 'Sleep', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '69-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-30 19:55:28', '2018-09-30 19:55:28', '', 69, 'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/2018/09/30/69-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
